保守黨於2017年5月末舉行黨魁選舉之際，安布羅斯於同月中宣布在國會夏季休會時（即新黨魁就任後數星期）辭去眾議院議席<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/rona-ambrose-conservative-mp-1.4116233|title='It's been an amazing experience': Rona Ambrose set to leave federal politics|work=CBC News|accessdate=2017-07-07|date=2017-05-15|first=John Paul|last=Tasker|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129183114/https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/rona-ambrose-conservative-mp-1.4116233|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/3453164/rona-ambrose-leaving-federal-politics/|title=Interim Conservative leader Rona Ambrose to announce resignation|work=The Canadian Press|first=Stephanie|last=Levitz|publisher=Global News|accessdate=2017-07-07|date=2017-05-16|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210124004750/https://globalnews.ca/news/3453164/rona-ambrose-leaving-federal-politics/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。她轉到[[伍德羅·威爾遜國際學者中心|伍德羅·威爾遜國際學者中心]]的加拿大學院擔當客席研究員，主力研究加美貿易關係並向兩國官員推廣[[北美自由貿易協議|北美自由貿易]]的好處<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ottawacitizen.com/news/politics/ambrose-confirms-departure-conservative-leader-to-join-washington-think-tank|title=Ambrose confirms departure, Conservative leader to join Washington think tank|last=Wingrove|first=Josh|date=May 16, 2017|work=Ottawa Citizen|access-date=May 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629185951/https://ottawacitizen.com/news/politics/ambrose-confirms-departure-conservative-leader-to-join-washington-think-tank|archive-date=2019-06-29|dead-url=no|agency=Bloomberg News|language=en}}</ref>。安布羅斯又表示雖然她本人支持亞伯達省的兩個主要右翼政黨亞伯達進步保守黨和野玫瑰黨合併，但她無意角逐合併後新政黨的黨魁職位<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/ambrose-pc-wildrose-merger-1.4121908|title=Rona Ambrose says proposed PC-Wildrose merger what Alberta needs|work=CBC News|accessdate=2017-07-07|date=2017-05-18|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112025136/https://www.cbc.ca/news/politics/ambrose-pc-wildrose-merger-1.4121908|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

